						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1456, Jaya, Āśvayuja, ba. 12,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1534 October 18, Sunday</hi> (not verifiable), in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Achyutarāya-Mahārāya.</hi> It registers a gift for the service of the god Hiriya-Tiruvēṅgaḷanātha of <hi rend="bold">Mūdaṇagiri.</hi> The gift was made for the merit of the king.</p>						

